summary: In Infinity War, Dr. Strange said only one outcome would win and then he proceeded to give Thanos the stone to save Tony’s life...
body:
In Infinity War, Dr. Strange said only one outcome would win and then he proceeded to give Thanos the stone to save Tony’s life and said, “We’re in the Endgame now.”

It was then that I had a premonition that Tony Stark would be integral to the defeat of Thanos. Because why would Dr. Strange, who barely knows Tony Stark and has only ever had scenes of tension with the guy, suddenly risk our realities and give up his duty to protect the Time Stone to save Tony. He knew.

But, I wasn’t sure of Tony’s fate until….

8 months later. The final movie title dropped.

I just knew that he would sacrifice himself in some way. Because the title of the movie was “Avengers: Endgame” and they said it would be the “end of an era.” And that’s what Dr. Strange said to Tony. Because he knew.

Because Tony Stark never backs down and never stops trying to protect and save the people he loves. Even at the cost of himself.

Love you 3000, Tones.

summary:
This is probably going to be just some bullshit idea but: 
What if the universe where the MCU Endgame happened isn’t where they...
body:
This is probably going to be just some bullshit idea but:

What if the universe where the MCU Endgame happened isn’t where they win, like, Strange was looking for one where everyone lived, including tony. Maybe Tony didn’t have to die but that was such an odd possibility, maybe that moment between strange and tony looking at each other and Stephen holding up one finger was more of a way of just accepting what was about to come. Maybe a lie so tony could feel more at peace w/ dying. Maybe it was a way for Stephen to recognize that Tony Stark, earths best defender, was about to go away for good, that strange had failed him and he was so very sorry.
